AB  - The mechanisms for insuring investments in stocks and bonds against depreciation have grown rapidly in the last decade. Insuring a portfolio entails managing it in such a way that the left hand tail of the return distribution is truncated. The present paper demonstrates how this may be achieved for fixed interest securities. Discrete time hedging procedures are derived with the inclusion of transaction costs.
